    "steps": [
      {
        "stepNumber": 1,
        "instructions": "• Finely chop cucumber and garlic. Thinly slice spring onion and brown onion (see ingredients). Grate carrot."
      },
      {
        "stepNumber": 2,
        "instructions": "• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook carrot and onion until tender, 3-4 mins. • Add pulled pork, Mexican seasoning, tomato paste and garlic, stirring, until fragrant, 1-2 mins. • Stir in the water, butter and stock powder and simmer, until slightly reduced, 1-2 mins. Season to taste. (Add more water if the pork looks dry!)"
      },
      {
        "stepNumber": 3,
        "instructions": "• Set air fryer to 200°C. Line base of air fryer basket with foil. Lay mini flour tortillas on a chopping board. Spoon pork mixture down the centre. • Roll tortillas up tightly and place, seam-side down, in air fryer basket. Spray or brush with olive oil. • Cook taquitos (in batches) until golden, 6-8 mins. NO AIR FRYER? Preheat grill to high. Place taquitos seam-side down in a medium baking dish, ensuring they fit snugly. Brush or spray with olive oil and grill until warmed through and golden, 5-8 mins."
      },
      {
        "stepNumber": 4,
        "instructions": "• In a small bowl, combine cucumber, spring onion and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season. • Divide Mexican pulled pork taquitos between plates. Drizzle over mayonnaise. Top with cucumber salsa."
      }
